        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer993879556" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1535087824129833624">Flannery O&apos;Connor taps into a different type of dark with this collection of ten short stories.  This is not horror, but it is disturbing.  Nothing uplifting in here, no sirree-bob.  <br/><br/>Hidden deformities, unwelcome visitors who refuse to leave, a woman&apos;s aversion to doctors, and a door-to-door Bible salesman who is a collector of some very odd things.  Many of the characters are slightly &quot;off&quot;, just as many have a mean streak.  Eyes play a prominent role, a cast in the eye, a cracked eye, the eyes</span>
  <span id="freeText1535087824129833624" style="display:none">Flannery O'Connor taps into a different type of dark with this collection of ten short stories.  This is not horror, but it is disturbing.  Nothing uplifting in here, no sirree-bob.  <br /><br />Hidden deformities, unwelcome visitors who refuse to leave, a woman's aversion to doctors, and a door-to-door Bible salesman who is a collector of some very odd things.  Many of the characters are slightly "off", just as many have a mean streak.  Eyes play a prominent role, a cast in the eye, a cracked eye, the eyes in the tail of a peacock, the look of the eyes behind spectacles. <br /><br />A Good Man Is Hard To Find title story is just as striking as I've always heard.  It may stick with me longer than I want.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1535087824129833624" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
